sub_title: Regional Offline Manager Europe for Singapore Airlines
summary:
Regional Offline Manager for Singapore Airlines covering 29 countries in Europe, including Israel, Tunisia, Algeria and Morocco. 

The main objective is to grow our presence in the offline region and to develop strategies which lead to an increase of our passenger sales revenue, the SIA brand awareness and to improve our relationship and communications with media and other stakeholders. 

Leading a dedicated team of professionals to provide full assistance and guidance to 9 General Sales Offices in the region.    

Experience in destination marketing, developing new market segments, advertising and promotional activities, coaching and training, IATA/BSP related issues and all other matters involving the day to day activities at an airline office.

Receiving 25 awards in the Benelux over the last 20 years.
